sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as KServe Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    participant vLLM as vllm-gaudi Pod<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant HPU as Intel Gaudi HPU<br/>Synapse AI 1.23.0
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>S3/PVC 443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over vLLM,Storage: Flow 1: Model Loading (Startup)
    vLLM->>Storage: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, AWS IAM
    Storage-->>vLLM: Model artifacts
    vLLM->>HPU: Load model to HPU memory<br/>HPU Device API
    HPU-->>vLLM: Model ready

    Note over Client,HPU: Flow 2: Single-HPU Inference Request
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.3, Bearer Token
    Gateway->>vLLM: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8000, plaintext (in-cluster)
    vLLM->>HPU: Execute forward pass<br/>HPU API (bucketed, compiled graphs)
    HPU-->>vLLM: Generated tokens
    vLLM-->>Gateway: JSON Response (streaming/batch)
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response<br/>TLS 1.3

    Note over vLLM,HPU: Flow 3: Multi-HPU Tensor Parallel
    participant HPU2 as Peer HPU Workers<br/>Dynamic Port HCCL/TCP

    vLLM->>HPU: Forward pass (driver worker)
    vLLM->>HPU2: all-reduce / all-gather<br/>HCCL/TCP, plaintext
    HPU2-->>vLLM: Synchronized tensors<br/>HCCL/TCP, plaintext

    Note over vLLM,HPU2: Flow 4: Disaggregated Prefill/Decode (NIXL)
    participant Decode as Decode Worker<br/>Dynamic Port NIXL/TCP

    vLLM->>vLLM: Prefill: compute KV-cache
    vLLM->>Decode: Transfer KV-cache blocks<br/>NIXL/TCP, plaintext
    Decode-->>Client: Continue generation<br/>via Gateway
